name: Handlebar Coffee Roasters
directions: When entering from Canon Perdido St (the only entrance), follow the alley with outside seating on the right side of the shop. Enter through the third doorway (the white painted doorway without a door). Through the doorway on your left, you will see the main espresso counter. The restroom is on your right, labeled “Toilet”.
comment:
There is only one restroom, and as it serves both staff and customers there is a likelihood of having someone waiting for the restroom. The outdoor entrance makes this restroom easy to use for anyone who does not wish to buy a coffee or pastry. However I would strongly recommend both. The light is on the right side of the door, just depress the button on the lower portion of the motion sensored switch. 
Handlebar Coffee Roasters offers free refills for any customer who orders plain coffee. Filtered water is available on tap for all customers, just ask a barista and they will direct you. The staff are friendly and helpful. There are outlets available in the outdoor seating area, and there is free WiFi available (just ask a barista for the password). The shop can be busy, but the staff are very competent with many orders.

name: REI
directions: The restrooms are at the back of the store.
comment: The restrooms are gendered and not single occupancy. The men’s room has one stall and one urinal. Depending on the time of day, REI can be nearly empty of customers, so pretend to browse as the restrooms are meant for customers only. Although the restrooms are not single occupancy, they appear to be safe and the staff are friendly but not intrusive.

name: Santa Barbara Roasting Company
directions: Upon entrance, continue straight. The two unisex restrooms are on the left and right past the espresso counter.
comment: As of October 30, 2017, the code for both restrooms is 2145. The restrooms are for customers, however the shop should be fairly busy depending on the time of day. Many people make use of the free WiFi, so if you take a seat, fill up your water bottle with the free water available in the seating area, and/or use one of the many outlets to charge your phone, it is likely that you will go unnoticed. I did notice that the soap dispenser (at least in the restroom on the right) may be out of reach for people with certain disabilities.
